============================================================
Processing step: QA the entire product to verify that all functionalities are working as expected.
============================================================

Result for step:
To QA the entire product and verify that all functionalities are working as expected, you would follow these steps:

1. Identify all the different functionalities or features of the product based on the user stories.
2. Create test cases for each feature by organizing similar user stories into cohesive groups.
3. Execute the test cases to ensure that each feature works as intended and that all requirements are met.
4. Document any issues or bugs found during testing.
5. Work with the development team to resolve any issues and retest the affected features.
6. Repeat the testing process until all functionalities are working as expected.
7. Provide a report on the test results, highlighting any issues found and their resolutions.

By organizing similar user stories into cohesive groups and testing each feature based on those groupings, you can thoroughly QA the entire product to ensure that all functionalities are working correctly.

